This is dotfiles for Zou,Ying.

This is configuration for zouying.

Installation:
    $ git clone https://github.com/xpzouying/dotfiles.git
    $ sh install.sh

    Open vim, and install plugins.
    $ vim
    :PluginInstall

    Finished installation.


1. The install.sh will install: git, vim, curl, zsh, ack-grep(ack).
2. Link some config file at $HOME: zshrc, vimrc, gitconfig, vimrc.bundles.
3. Modify terminal colors to support 256 colors. Use `tput colors` to check.

NOTE:

To support vim plugins perfectly, may need to install powerline_font(Inconsolata
for Powerline) in "tools\" directory manually.

####################
## Backup ##

NOTE:
0. Pre-install (for ubuntu):
    sudo apt-get install vim git curl zsh

1. For zsh, using oh-my-zs .
    -- via curl:
        curl -L http://install.ohmyz.sh | sh

    -- via wget:
        wget --no-check-certificate http://install.ohmyz.sh -O - | sh

    After install oh-my-zsh,
        $ sudo chsh -s $(which zsh) $(whoami)
    Change default bash in /etc/passwd:
        $(whoami):.../usr/bin/zsh

2. Install 'ack-grep'
    Installation for Ubuntu:
        sudo apt-get install ack-grep

    Rename ack:
       sudo dpkg-divert --local --divert /usr/bin/ack --rename --add /usr/bin/ack-grep

3. Install Vundle:
    git clone https://github.com/gmarik/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim

4. PluginInstall:
    Open vim, then:
        :PluginInstall


######
Install powerline fonts:
    git clone https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline-fonts.git
